<title>POLAND: Zabrze finalises GM plant deal.</title>
<headline>Zabrze finalises GM plant deal.</headline>
<dateline>WARSAW 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Polish construction company Mostostal-Zabrze has signed an 87.6-million-mark contract to build a plant for Germany's Adam Opel AG, a General Motors Corp unit, Mostostal said in a statement on Tuesday.</p>
<p>Last week Mostostal said Opel would award it a 90 million mark contract to build the Opel plant.</p>
<p>The contract encompasses the construction of the main buildings of the 500 million mark car factory, located in the southern town of Gliwice, to be completed in the first half of 1998.</p>
<p>The car plant is to employ 2,000 and assemble 72,000 vehicles annually.</p>
<p>Last year, Mostostal Zabrze signed a 17 million mark contract with Adam Opel for another construction project at the site.</p>
<p>-- Warsaw Newsroom +48 22 653 9700</p>
